"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-2024-04-10-2024-summer-olympics-track-and-field-prize-money\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"For the first time, some winners at this summer's Olympics in Paris will take home more than a gold medal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 62, \"end\": 67, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999961354935388, \"rank\": 3.8645214256315386e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 4, \"to\": 18}, {\"ngram\": \"some winners\", \"from\": 20, \"to\": 32}, {\"ngram\": \"this summer's Olympics\", \"from\": 36, \"to\": 58}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athletics, the governing body for track and field,announced Wednesdaythat it has established a prize fund of $2.4 million that will be used to award $50,000 to the gold medalists in each of the 48 athletics events scheduled for the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 108, \"end\": 123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 370, \"end\": 375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999961354935388, \"rank\": 3.8645214256315386e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the governing body\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 143}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 148, \"to\": 153}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 163}, {\"ngram\": \"Wednesdaythat\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 187}, {\"ngram\": \"a prize fund\", \"from\": 207, \"to\": 219}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medalists\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 292}, {\"ngram\": \"the 48 athletics events\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 327}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 366}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It marks the first time that prize money has been offered to Olympians by a sport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s governing body.\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 478, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 400}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 417}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s governing body\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many countries and national Olympic committees offer payments to medalists, but World Athletics will be the first federation to reward winners with cash prizes.\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 560, \"end\": 575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many countries\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 494}, {\"ngram\": \"national Olympic committees\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"payments\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 541}, {\"ngram\": \"medalists\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 554}, {\"ngram\": \"the first federation\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 604}, {\"ngram\": \"winners\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"cash prizes\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 639}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Committee, for example, paid $37,500 to gold medalists at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021,according to the Associated Press.\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 775, \"end\": 791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999833274455974, \"rank\": 1.4668989113757963e-05, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Committee\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medalists\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While only gold medalists will receive payouts this year, World Athletics announced a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cfirm commitment\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d to offer prizes to silver and bronze medalists at the 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 852, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999985001688735, \"rank\": 1.4196907171438156e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only gold medalists\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 819}, {\"ngram\": \"payouts\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cfirm commitment\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"prizes\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 917}, {\"ngram\": \"silver and bronze medalists\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Olympics\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhile it is impossible to put a marketable value on winning an Olympic medal, or on the commitment and focus it takes to even represent your country at an Olympic Games, I think it is important we start somewhere and make sure some of the revenues generated by our athletes at the Olympic Games are directly returned to those who make the Games the global spectacle that it is,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d World Athletics president Sebastian Coe said in a statement.\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1371, \"end\": 1386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 1397, \"end\": 1410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a marketable value\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1038}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"the commitment\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"your country\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1158}, {\"ngram\": \"the revenues\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1237}, {\"ngram\": \"our athletes\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1263}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1284}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1334}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1430}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The prize money will come from the revenue sharing funds that World Athletics receives from the International Olympic Committee every four years.\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1495, \"end\": 1510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 1529, \"end\": 1560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The prize money\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1448}, {\"ngram\": \"the revenue sharing funds\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1489}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medalists in individual events will receive the full $50,000, while winners in relay events will split the money.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gold medalists\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"individual events\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1614}, {\"ngram\": \"winners\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1659}, {\"ngram\": \"relay events\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"the money\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1725, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Loading recommendations\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations Dan Gartland writes Sports Illustrated\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s flagship daily newsletter, SI:AM, and is the host of the \\u00e2\\u00